The paper discusses the concept of Network Service Chaining (NSC) in the context of carrier-grade telecommunication networks, which falls under the category of Networked and Distributed Systems (cs.NI). The paper also addresses security considerations, which suggests the category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). The paper discusses the design considerations and system requirements for NSC, which could fall under the category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the challenges in the lifecycle of a network service chain, which could fall under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper discusses the advantages of adopting NSC, which could fall under the category of Computer Engineering (cs.CE).
